Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00m5fb2
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 20 Dec 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Doctor Arash Hejazi tells Outlook about the death threats he got after he was seen trying to save the life of Neda Agha-Soltan, the young Iranian woman who was killed during the protests of 2009. Also in the programme, the Kenyan dancer teaching ballet to boys and girls in the slums of Nairobi. And British adventurer David Hempleman Adams and his daughter Amelia talk about their record breaking trip to the South Pole. Show less